00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:51,360
plotting an EMA of the highs and an EMA

271
00:12:48,160 --> 00:12:54,399
of the lows. So, you get two lines that

272
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:57,279
frame price. This acts like a dynamic

273
00:12:54,399 --> 00:12:59,600
band of support and resistance. On its

274
00:12:57,279 --> 00:13:02,639
own, this channel might not be as

275
00:12:59,600 --> 00:13:05,279
reliable, but in combination with static

276
00:13:02,639 --> 00:13:07,760
support and resistance level like round

277
00:13:05,279 --> 00:13:10,800
numbers, this channel becomes very

278
00:13:07,760 --> 00:13:13,279
important. Many traders fixate on these

279
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:16,240
levels. They often place stops or

280
00:13:13,279 --> 00:13:19,519
entries around them. So price can pause

281
00:13:16,240 --> 00:13:22,480
or bounce at round numbers. Sometimes

282
00:13:19,519 --> 00:13:24,240
big players place large orders there,

283
00:13:22,480 --> 00:13:27,040
turning them into supply or demand

284
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:29,200
zones. If the price is above the

285
00:13:27,040 --> 00:13:31,600
channel, you might see a bullish

286
00:13:29,200 --> 00:13:34,079
environment. So, you look for long

287
00:13:31,600 --> 00:13:37,680
trades at the next round number bounce

288
00:13:34,079 --> 00:13:40,480
or break. If price is below the channel,

289
00:13:37,680 --> 00:13:43,680
you likely see a bearish environment, so

290
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:46,800
you aim for short trades. First, check

291
00:13:43,680 --> 00:13:50,079
if price is above or below the channel.

292
00:13:46,800 --> 00:13:53,200
If above, the trend is presumably up. If

293
00:13:50,079 --> 00:13:55,760
below, the trend is presumably down. If

294
00:13:53,200 --> 00:13:57,360
price is inside the channel, it might be

295
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:59,680
consolidating.

296
00:13:57,360 --> 00:14:02,240
Then you see where the nearest big round

297
00:13:59,680 --> 00:14:04,639
numbers lie. If the market is in an

298
00:14:02,240 --> 00:14:07,440
uptrend, you might plan to buy a

299
00:14:04,639 --> 00:14:10,000
breakout above the round number. If the

300
00:14:07,440 --> 00:14:13,600
market is in a downtrend, you might plan

301
00:14:10,000 --> 00:14:16,079
to sell a breakout below a round number.

302
00:14:13,600 --> 00:14:19,519
The channel can also serve as dynamic

303
00:14:16,079 --> 00:14:21,680
support or resistance. If price keeps

304
00:14:19,519 --> 00:14:24,000
bouncing off the upper boundary of the

305
00:14:21,680 --> 00:14:26,800
channel, that can confirm bullish

306
00:14:24,000 --> 00:14:29,519
momentum. If it keeps failing at the

307
00:14:26,800 --> 00:14:31,199
lower boundary, that can confirm a

308
00:14:29,519 --> 00:14:33,760
downtrend.

309
00:14:31,199 --> 00:14:36,959
Sometimes this channel acts as a

310
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:39,760
trampoline. Price will break through,

311
00:14:36,959 --> 00:14:42,880
come back to test an EMA line, and

312
00:14:39,760 --> 00:14:46,079
bounce away if the trend is intact. If

313
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:48,639
it fails to bounce and instead lingers,

314
00:14:46,079 --> 00:14:51,279
that might signal a shift.

315
00:14:48,639 --> 00:14:54,079
The first bounce is important. It proves

316
00:14:51,279 --> 00:14:56,160
that the channel is being respected.

317
00:14:54,079 --> 00:14:59,040
Then you look for a round number to

318
00:14:56,160 --> 00:15:02,399
align with that bounce. That confluence

319
00:14:59,040 --> 00:15:05,120
can yield a strong trade. For instance,

320
00:15:02,399 --> 00:15:08,560
a bull trend brings price to the top of

321
00:15:05,120 --> 00:15:10,720
the channel near a round number. If you

322
00:15:08,560 --> 00:15:14,000
see a bullish candlestick bounce off

323
00:15:10,720 --> 00:15:16,160
that zone, you jump in. You place a stop

324
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:19,360
under the channel and you target the

325
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:21,839
next round number above. If price

326
00:15:19,360 --> 00:15:24,079
meanders inside the channel for more

327
00:15:21,839 --> 00:15:27,839
than three candles, you might skip

328
00:15:24,079 --> 00:15:30,399
trades. That indicates indecision. It's

329
00:15:27,839 --> 00:15:33,199
possible the market is waiting for news

330
00:15:30,399 --> 00:15:35,440
or liquidity is low. You can wait for

331
00:15:33,199 --> 00:15:38,320
price to break out of the channel with

332
00:15:35,440 --> 00:15:40,480
conviction before acting. If you trade

333
00:15:38,320 --> 00:15:42,000
while the market is stuck, you might get

334
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:44,240
whipsaw.

335
00:15:42,000 --> 00:15:46,560
That's why the strategy says to watch

336
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:50,000
for immediate rejection or bounce

337
00:15:46,560 --> 00:15:53,839
behavior. You want clarity, not sideways

338
00:15:50,000 --> 00:15:57,120
chop. So, here's the plan. You identify

339
00:15:53,839 --> 00:15:59,920
the overall trend with the channel. You

340
00:15:57,120 --> 00:16:02,160
find the nearest round numbers. You then

341
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:05,199
wait for price to approach that round

342
00:16:02,160 --> 00:16:07,920
number with the channel as a guide. If

343
00:16:05,199 --> 00:16:10,720
the trend is up, look for a break above

344
00:16:07,920 --> 00:16:12,800
the round number or a bounce near the

345
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:16,000
channel that aligns with that round

346
00:16:12,800 --> 00:16:19,120
number. If the trend is down, look for a

347
00:16:16,000 --> 00:16:22,560
downside break of the round number or a

348
00:16:19,120 --> 00:16:24,079
bounce from the channel's underside.

349
00:16:22,560 --> 00:16:26,639
You can also trade different

350
00:16:24,079 --> 00:16:29,199
combinations using all the tools and

351
00:16:26,639 --> 00:16:31,920
indicators we've talked about. Some

352
00:16:29,199 --> 00:16:35,120
traders run into monthly pivots that

353
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:38,000
coincide with a round number or they see

354
00:16:35,120 --> 00:16:41,279
that a Ballinger band extreme lining up

355
00:16:38,000 --> 00:16:43,759
with a round number. Maybe price is at a

356
00:16:41,279 --> 00:16:46,639
monthly pivot at the third deviation

357
00:16:43,759 --> 00:16:49,839
Ballinger band or price is in an

358
00:16:46,639 --> 00:16:53,600
uptrend, holds above the monthly pivot

359
00:16:49,839 --> 00:16:55,440
and sits near the 21 EMA channel. The

360
00:16:53,600 --> 00:16:58,000
more confluence you have, the more

361
00:16:55,440 --> 00:17:00,880
conviction you might gain. Your job is

362
00:16:58,000 --> 00:17:03,759
to read the bigger story. Are we near a

363
00:17:00,880 --> 00:17:06,880
strong monthly pivot or a known supply

364
00:17:03,759 --> 00:17:10,480
demand zone? Do the Ballinger bands show

365
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:13,520
an extreme or a comfortable trend push?

366
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:16,240
Are we flirting with a big round number?

367
00:17:13,520 --> 00:17:18,319
If multiple elements line up, you have a

368
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:20,160
potent setup.

369
00:17:18,319 --> 00:17:22,880
Imagine you start your swing trading

370
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:25,439
routine on a Sunday. You check the

371
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:28,160
weekly and daily charts. You note the

372
00:17:25,439 --> 00:17:30,799
monthly pivot lines. Then you switch on

373
00:17:28,160 --> 00:17:33,679
the three Ballinger bands. You see that

374
00:17:30,799 --> 00:17:36,480
price is currently near the middle band

375
00:17:33,679 --> 00:17:39,440
slightly above it. That suggests a

376
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:42,559
bullish posture. You may notice a big

377
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:45,280
round number which may or may not align

378
00:17:42,559 --> 00:17:48,000
with the monthly pivot. Then you track

379
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:50,240
the candles to see if a bounce or a

380
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:52,559
breakout occurs there.

381
00:17:50,240 --> 00:17:55,360
This approach is perfect for beginners

382
00:17:52,559 --> 00:17:58,559
or traders that don't have much time to

383
00:17:55,360 --> 00:18:01,120
trade. You do not rely on guesswork. You

384
00:17:58,559 --> 00:18:04,960
have specific levels to watch. Monthly

385
00:18:01,120 --> 00:18:07,919
pivots, Ballinger bands, or the 21 EMA

386
00:18:04,960 --> 00:18:10,640
channel. As a swing trader, you can

387
00:18:07,919 --> 00:18:13,280
check the chart once or twice a day. You

388
00:18:10,640 --> 00:18:16,000
do not need to watch every minute. You

389
00:18:13,280 --> 00:18:18,640
can quickly spot potential setups, place

390
00:18:16,000 --> 00:18:21,679
alerts, and plan your trades in a

391
00:18:18,640 --> 00:18:24,720
structured way. Sometimes you see many

392
00:18:21,679 --> 00:18:27,600
lines, the pivots, the channel, plus

393
00:18:24,720 --> 00:18:30,799
multiple round numbers that can clutter

394
00:18:27,600 --> 00:18:33,440
your chart. You must prioritize. If

395
00:18:30,799 --> 00:18:36,960
you're aimed at a bullish trade, focus

396
00:18:33,440 --> 00:18:39,679
on major support pivots or lower band,

397
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:42,400
not everything. If it sets up with a

398
00:18:39,679 --> 00:18:45,360
clear confluence like the pivot plus a

399
00:18:42,400 --> 00:18:47,919
round number, then that's enough. Do not

400
00:18:45,360 --> 00:18:51,760
chase every minor pivot or Ballinger

401
00:18:47,919 --> 00:18:54,240
band and plan your trades in advance.

402
00:18:51,760 --> 00:18:56,400
Wait for price to come to your zone.

403
00:18:54,240 --> 00:18:59,039
Then watch for a candlestick pattern

404
00:18:56,400 --> 00:19:01,200
that confirms your direction. This

405
00:18:59,039 --> 00:19:03,360
patience can help you avoid random

406
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:04,960
trades that do not align with your

407
00:19:03,360 --> 00:19:07,520
strategy.

408
00:19:04,960 --> 00:19:10,160
Some swing traders like to check if

409
00:19:07,520 --> 00:19:11,919
