414
00:19:20,799 --> 00:19:26,559
you. Some prefer pure technical reading.

415
00:19:24,320 --> 00:19:29,679
Others keep an eye on the calendar to

416
00:19:26,559 --> 00:19:31,440
dodge big surprises. That is personal

417
00:19:29,679 --> 00:19:35,200
preference.

418
00:19:31,440 --> 00:19:38,000
Now on daily or 4hour charts, the candle

419
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:40,799
close can be pivotal. If you see price

420
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:44,000
bouncing off the pivot intraday, but the

421
00:19:40,799 --> 00:19:46,799
daily close fails to hold, that might be

422
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:49,760
a warning sign. Wait until the close

423
00:19:46,799 --> 00:19:53,039
might confirm the bounce is real. That's

424
00:19:49,760 --> 00:19:55,840
how you filter out noise. For instance,

425
00:19:53,039 --> 00:19:58,160
if price wicks below the monthly pivot

426
00:19:55,840 --> 00:20:01,200
but closes above it with a bullish

427
00:19:58,160 --> 00:20:04,160
candlestick, that pivot bounce is more

428
00:20:01,200 --> 00:20:07,840
convincing. If price wicks above the

429
00:20:04,160 --> 00:20:10,799
pivot but closes below, that is a fail.

430
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:14,000
The same logic goes for the 21 EMA

431
00:20:10,799 --> 00:20:17,200
channel. If price intraday dips inside

432
00:20:14,000 --> 00:20:20,160
the channel but then closes back above,

433
00:20:17,200 --> 00:20:22,640
that might reinforce the uptrend. If it

434
00:20:20,160 --> 00:20:25,840
closes below the channel, that might be

435
00:20:22,640 --> 00:20:28,480
a shift. In practice, you can scroll

436
00:20:25,840 --> 00:20:30,480
through charts from prior months. You

437
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:33,440
can see how the monthly pivot lines

438
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:36,559
shaped the market. You can spot how many

439
00:20:33,440 --> 00:20:39,120
times price reversed near these lines or

440
00:20:36,559 --> 00:20:41,760
how breakouts occurred. Then you can

441
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:44,480
plot your Ballinger bands and watch how

442
00:20:41,760 --> 00:20:47,360
price interacts with them. Do you see

443
00:20:44,480 --> 00:20:50,960
consistent bounces off the middle band?

444
00:20:47,360 --> 00:20:53,840
The same goes for the 21 EMA channel.

445
00:20:50,960 --> 00:20:57,039
Observe and note how often price bounces

446
00:20:53,840 --> 00:20:59,360
off the top or bottom line.

447
00:20:57,039 --> 00:21:02,559
Now, here are some potential pitfalls

448
00:20:59,360 --> 00:21:05,840
you may encounter and their solutions.

449
00:21:02,559 --> 00:21:08,559
First one, over complication. If you try

450
00:21:05,840 --> 00:21:12,400
to watch too many lines, you might get

451
00:21:08,559 --> 00:21:15,120
confused. So, simplify. Choose only one

452
00:21:12,400 --> 00:21:17,440
dynamic support and resistance zone.

453
00:21:15,120 --> 00:21:20,960
Choose between the Ballinger bands or

454
00:21:17,440 --> 00:21:23,120
the EMA channel and focus on the zones

455
00:21:20,960 --> 00:21:24,720
with the highest overlap or

456
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:27,039
significance.

457
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:29,919
Another pitfall is not waiting for

458
00:21:27,039 --> 00:21:33,760
confirmation. Jumping in without seeing

459
00:21:29,919 --> 00:21:35,840
a candle close might lead to fake outs.

460
00:21:33,760 --> 00:21:37,440
Wait for that bounce or break to

461
00:21:35,840 --> 00:21:39,840
confirm.

462
00:21:37,440 --> 00:21:42,720
Most common problem is fading a strong

463
00:21:39,840 --> 00:21:45,280
trend without care. If price is

464
00:21:42,720 --> 00:21:47,520
rocketing upward, you might not want to

465
00:21:45,280 --> 00:21:50,480
short just because it hits the outer

466
00:21:47,520 --> 00:21:53,600
Ballinger band. Check if volume is still

467
00:21:50,480 --> 00:21:56,320
surging, if the pivot is truly holding,

468
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:59,120
or if there's a supply zone. Another

469
00:21:56,320 --> 00:22:02,240
problem, when swing trading, you'll have

470
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:04,880
a tendency to let your losers run. I

471
00:22:02,240 --> 00:22:07,600
want you to respect your stops. If price

472
00:22:04,880 --> 00:22:11,679
breaks the pivot you used as support,

473
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:14,400
let it go. The initial idea is invalid.

474
00:22:11,679 --> 00:22:17,280
Sometimes you'll face a gap open or a

475
00:22:14,400 --> 00:22:19,520
surprise news event that sends price far

476
00:22:17,280 --> 00:22:22,559
beyond your pivot or your Ballinger

477
00:22:19,520 --> 00:22:25,200
band. That can happen after weekends or

478
00:22:22,559 --> 00:22:28,240
major announcements. In that case,

479
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:31,520
re-evaluate. If price already soared

480
00:22:28,240 --> 00:22:35,120
past your pivot, do not chase. Wait for

481
00:22:31,520 --> 00:22:37,760
a retest or a new pivot to form. Swing

482
00:22:35,120 --> 00:22:40,960
trading thrives on patience. You do not

483
00:22:37,760 --> 00:22:42,880
have to be in a trade every single day.

484
00:22:40,960 --> 00:22:44,559
Another challenge you'll face,

485
00:22:42,880 --> 00:22:47,200
especially if you are used to day

486
00:22:44,559 --> 00:22:50,159
trading, is the impulse to act onto

487
00:22:47,200 --> 00:22:52,720
every minimal movement. Swing trading

488
00:22:50,159 --> 00:22:55,679
calls for a calmer state. You don't need

489
00:22:52,720 --> 00:22:58,640
to act every day. You pick your level.

490
00:22:55,679 --> 00:23:01,120
You wait sometimes multiple days for

491
00:22:58,640 --> 00:23:04,559
price to get there. You see if it sets

492
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:07,600
up. If not, you skip it. That's the

493
00:23:04,559 --> 00:23:10,720
discipline part. Another psychological

494
00:23:07,600 --> 00:23:13,520
element is trusting your pivot or your

495
00:23:10,720 --> 00:23:16,400
channel. If you set your stop under that

496
00:23:13,520 --> 00:23:19,360
pivot, do not move it if price is

497
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:21,760
approaching. If the pivot fails, then

498
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:24,320
you accept the loss. That's how you keep

499
00:23:21,760 --> 00:23:28,080
your risk controlled. Emotional changes

500
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:30,559
to your plan might cause bigger losses.

501
00:23:28,080 --> 00:23:33,039
Handling emotional swings is another

502
00:23:30,559 --> 00:23:36,320
challenge. You might see a position in

503
00:23:33,039 --> 00:23:39,039
profit for a few days and suddenly the

504
00:23:36,320 --> 00:23:41,840
market retraces. If you are not used to

505
00:23:39,039 --> 00:23:45,039
this dynamic, you could panic. But these

506
00:23:41,840 --> 00:23:47,440
swings are normal in a multi-day trade.

507
00:23:45,039 --> 00:23:51,360
That is why you trust your pivot or your

508
00:23:47,440 --> 00:23:54,880
channel. If it holds, you stay. If price

509
00:23:51,360 --> 00:23:57,360
breaks, you exit. Many traders even set

510
00:23:54,880 --> 00:24:00,880
alerts so they do not watch every

511
00:23:57,360 --> 00:24:04,000
candle. they just get notified if price

512
00:24:00,880 --> 00:24:06,080
hits a pivot or breaks a channel.

513
00:24:04,000 --> 00:24:08,720
Another challenge will be finding the

514
00:24:06,080 --> 00:24:11,360
correct exit points. One method is to

515
00:24:08,720 --> 00:24:13,760
aim for the next pivot level. If you

516
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:18,080
bought near the main pivot, you might

517
00:24:13,760 --> 00:24:21,279
target R1 or R2 if the trend cooperates.

518
00:24:18,080 --> 00:24:24,880
If you shorted near R1, you might target

519
00:24:21,279 --> 00:24:27,679
the main pivot or S1. Another method is

520
00:24:24,880 --> 00:24:29,840
to use the Ballinger bands. If you fade

521
00:24:27,679 --> 00:24:33,279
an extreme near the third deviation

522
00:24:29,840 --> 00:24:36,159
band, you might aim for the middle band.

523
00:24:33,279 --> 00:24:38,799
Keep a record of each swing trade. Write

524
00:24:36,159 --> 00:24:41,039
down the reason you took it. Did it rely

525
00:24:38,799 --> 00:24:44,000
on the monthly pivot plus a round

526
00:24:41,039 --> 00:24:47,360
number? Did it rely on a Ballinger band

527
00:24:44,000 --> 00:24:50,159
bounce? Note your stop, your target, and

528
00:24:47,360 --> 00:24:53,200
the outcome. This helps you see which

529
00:24:50,159 --> 00:24:55,840
setups produce the best results. Over

530
00:24:53,200 --> 00:24:58,159
time, you refine your approach. And if

531
00:24:55,840 --> 00:25:00,640
you're ready to fit this into a full a

532
00:24:58,159 --> 00:25:02,880
toz trading system, that's what our

533
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:05,880
academy is for. Link is in the

534
00:25:02,880 --> 00:25:05,880
description.

